cova.data

Class WrappedTaintSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • cova.data.WrappedTaintSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<AbstractTaint>

    public class WrappedTaintSet
extends Object
implements Iterable<AbstractTaint>
    The Class WrappedTaintSet is a container of taint set.

    It provides all operations that can be done to the taint set.

      • getMissingConstraint

        public static IConstraint getMissingConstraint(Set<AbstractTaint> taints,
                                               IConstraint constraintOfStmt)
        This method check if the taint set with the same access path is complete, which means the union(or-operation) of all constraints, say b, should be equal to the constraint of the statement c. If it is not complete, return the missing constraint a. The missing constraint can be computed by (c v -b) due to the following derivation.

        a v b = c
        a v (b v -b) = c v -b
        a v true = c v -b
        a = c v -b

        Parameters:
        taints - the taints
        constraintOfStmt - the constraint of the statement
        Returns:
        the missing constraint
